{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "e0a1f3b0-0000-4000-8000-c0a1f3b0e080",
    "name": "log-remediation-service (P6.1a cross-phase closer)",
    "description": "Postman v2.1 collection for log-remediation-service after P6.0/P6.1/P6.2/P6.3 + P6.0a strict-rules cleanup + P6.1a cross-phase closer on :8096. log-remediation-service has NO business REST surface -- it is a Spring for Apache Kafka consumer that drains cortex.anomalies.v1 (CloudEvents 1.0 structured-mode JSON envelopes produced by log-processor-service per ADR-0031) and fans out to the configured channel adapter (slack/pagerduty/jira/noop, gated by cortex.remediation.dispatcher.provider per ADR-0032 D1). The only HTTP surface is actuator (health/liveness/readiness/info/metrics/prometheus/beans) + the channel-shaped POSTs into a local WireMock at :8094 (smoke-only flavour, NOT a real Slack / PagerDuty / Jira call). Folder order: Admin asserts actuator + Prometheus exposition; Metrics-Baseline snapshots the dispatched_total{channel,outcome,tenant_id} counter for each channel; Channel-Mock-Smoke fires the WireMock-shaped POSTs that scripts/smoke-p6-1a.ps1 uses internally (so the Postman + Newman path stays in lock-step with the smoke per LD23); Metrics-After does NOT assert deltas (Postman cannot publish to Kafka so the dispatched counter does not tick from Postman alone -- the smoke script is the closed loop that proves the e2e counter increment). Boot the service + Kafka + WireMock first with scripts/smoke-p6-1a.ps1 -Provider all (Leg B), then run this collection against the still-running stack for the Leg C contract.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "if (!pm.variables.get('request_id')) {",
          "    pm.variables.set('request_id', 'pm-' + Math.random().toString(36).substring(2, 12));",
          "}",
          "pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'X-Request-Id', value: pm.variables.get('request_id') });",
          "pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'X-Correlation-ID', value: pm.variables.get('request_id') });",
          "const tenant = pm.environment.get('tenant_id');",
          "if (tenant) { pm.request.headers.upsert({ key: 'X-Tenant-Id', value: tenant }); }"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "listen": "test",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "pm.test('response under 5000 ms (actuator + mock-server tolerated)', function () {",
          "    pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(5000);",
          "});"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
